cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on face alignment using heatmap regression, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel loss function and discusses the use of neural networks, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions experiments on different benchmarks, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. Finally, the use of neural networks and loss functions also falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
